  <h3>Button Groups</h3>
  <p> we can group buttons in 3 different ways </p>
  <h4>First type of grouping default is :</h4>
  <div class="btn-group btn-group-lg">
    <!-- we can specify the button width size here -->
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info"> Elon Musk</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Bill gates</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning">Mark</button>
  </div>
  <br>
  <h4>SECOND VERTICAL TYPE: </h4>
  <div class="btn-group-vertical btn-group-lg">
    <!-- we can specify the button width size here -->
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Elon Musk</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Bill gates</button>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning">Mark</button>
  </div>
  <h4>THIRD JUSTIFIED TYPE :</h4>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="btn-group btn-group-justified">
      <div class="btn-group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Elon Musk</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Bill gates</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Mark</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <p> we can also mix input groups with button groups</p>
  <div class="btn-toolbar mb-3" role="toolbar" aria-label="Toolbar with button groups">
   <div class="input-group">
     <span class="input-group-addon" id="btnGroupAddon">@</span>
     <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="dc.gov" aria-describedby="btnGroupAddon">
   </div>
  </div>
</div>
